{"questionId":"9082379","questionHtml":"<p>Two masses <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;are connected by a string over a frictionless pulley of negligible mass. The masses are released from rest. Air resistance is negligible.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/f6e395ee29a065b22a04e77f7329b80c79ad2662.png\"></p>\n<p>Mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;accelerates downwards at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>. What is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math>?<br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; 2</p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; 3</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9082379","referenceCode":"22M.1A.SL.TZ1.7","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Two masses m1 and m2 are connected by a string over a frictionless pulley of negligible mass. The masses are released from rest. Air resistance is negligible. Mass m2 accelerates d","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"7","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A.2 Forces and momentum"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}